Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createSpecialDrcRegion(25.10)                    createSpecialDrcRegion(25.10)

Name
       createSpecialDrcRegion - DRC region layers define a special masterslice
       layer  that  is  used to define the areas of a region on which a set of
       rules defined in the metal, cut, and/or trim metal layers with the  RE-
       GION property would be applied

Syntax
       createSpecialDrcRegion

       [-help]

       [-extendOuterX <float>]

       [-extendOuterY <float>]

       [-extendX <float>]

       [-extendY <float>]

       [-insts <string>]

       -layer <string>

       DRC  region  layers  define a special masterslice layer that is used to
       define the areas of a region on which a set of  rules  defined  in  the
       metal,  cut, and/or trim metal layers with the REGION property would be
       applied. The createSpecialDrcRegion command can be used to add drc  re-
       gion blockages in or around the die area except specified macros.

Parameters
       -extendOuterX <float>
              Expands the routing blockage in X direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendOuterY <float>
              Expands the routing blockage in Y direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendX <float>
              Expands the non-routing blockage in X direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -extendY <float>
              Expands the non-routing blockage in X direction.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each createSpecialDrcRegion parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createSpecialDrcRegion

       -insts <string>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance that are  to  be
              cut out.

              Note:  Wild  card  characters are not supported while specifying
              hierarchical instance names.

              Note: All blocks are included if -insts is not specified or when
              -insts{} is specified.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -layer <string>
              Specifies the names of the layers on which the routing  blockage
              is created.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The  following  command  creates a routing blockage on R1 that
                blocks out DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST:

                createSpecialDrcRegion -layer R1 -extendOutterX 10 -extendOut-
                terY 20 -insts DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST

              * The following command creates a routing blockage  on  R1  that
                blocks out DTMF_INST/RAM_256x16_TEST_INST/RAM_256x16_INST:

                createSpecialDrcRegion  -layer R1 -extendX 10 -extendY 20 -in-
                sts DTMF_INST/RAM_256x16_TEST_INST/RAM_256x16_INST

Related Information
